               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 3ra-16ra)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 16ra-42va)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     43ra-135vb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 43ra-52ra) 
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 53ra-56ra), preceded by an excerpt
                     from “Testament of Our Lord” (fol. 52rb-va)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady by
                     St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 56ra-67ra)
 III-4) Anaphora of St John the
                     Son of Thunder (fols. 67ra-76rb)
 III-5) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of
                     Cyprus (fols. 76rb-82ra)
 III-6) Anaphora of St Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy
                     of St Gregory”) (fols. 82ra-87va)
 III-7) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom
                     (fols. 87va-94ra)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols.
                     94ra-96vb)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 96vb-103ra)
                     III-10) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 103ra-110vb)
                     III-11) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols. 110vb-120va)
                     III-12) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols. 120va-126rb)
 III-13)
                     Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols. 126rb-132vb)
 III-14) Second
                     Anaphora of St Gregory (“Christmas-liturgy of St Gregory”) (fols.
                     132vb-135vb).</summary>
