                           <desc>- Ethiopic numerals written in vertical lines beside the drawing; several words (magic spell?) crudely written above the drawing: <locus target="#2r">fol.  2r</locus>. - European numerals, sometimes accompanied by Roman letters, crudely written above the text: fols. 3v, 4r, 4v, 5v, 6v, 7v, etc. (in the upper margin). - <locus target="#40rb">Fol.  40rb</locus>-va (the lower part of col. rb and the upper part of col. va) is left blank for unclear reasons. - Crude notes: fols. 67r, 73r, 76r, 82r, 87v, 96v, 103r, 111r, 121r, 126r, 133r (in the upper margin). - Some portions of the text are underlined with lilac ink (s. fols. 27ra-rb, 31rb, 33rb, 34rb, etc.). - Some portions of the text are written in compressed script (s. fols. 45v, 46r, 46v, etc.). - Immediate correction (word between two thin lines): <locus target="#123vb">fol.  123vb</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
